Super Eagles defender Chidozie Awaziem has assured Nigerians of the team’s readiness to face Egypt in today’s African Cup of Nations (AFCON) Group D opener at the Roumdé Adjia Stadium in Garoua. With the players knowing the importance of starting their AFCON campaign on a winning note, the  Alanyaspor center-back says the team is focused on the job at hand. “Everyone in the team right now is fully focussed, we are a few hours from the kick-off of our first game and everyone is concentrating on the game,” Awaziem told NFF TV.   Nigeria, Egypt live on StarTimes     Osimhen to under fresh tests today     Musa hints about AFCON farewell   The former Porto star admitted that today’s opener would not be a walk in the park but is confident that the team would get a positive result at the end of the day. - Advertisement - “We know it is not going to be an easy game because Egypt has a lot of good players but we are fully ready to battle against them and I know with the right effort from the coach, players and Nigerians, we would come out with a positive result.” He said. “Honestly, there is a really good positive feeling in the team. The group is a very wonderful group because everyone helps each other. We all carry each other along and I think it’s a really wonderful group. And I know with this feeling the team will go far in Cameroon.